{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01T11bSEA3w4Q1YB4MuyWA2U","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# -------------------------------\n     2→# Datasources\n     3→# -------------------------------\n     4→\n     5→# Dev: H2 in-memory database\n     6→%dev.quarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\n     7→%dev.quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:petclinic;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\n     8→%dev.quarkus.datasource.username=sa\n     9→%dev.quarkus.datasource.password=\n    10→\n    11→# Test: H2 in-memory database\n    12→%test.quarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\n    13→%test.quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:petclinic-test;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\n    14→%test.quarkus.datasource.username=sa\n    15→%test.quarkus.datasource.password=\n    16→\n    17→# Prod: PostgreSQL\n    18→%prod.quarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\n    19→%prod.quarkus.datasource.username=developer\n    20→%prod.quarkus.datasource.password=developer\n    21→%prod.quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://postgresql:5432/mydb\n    22→%prod.quarkus.datasource.jdbc.min-size=5\n    23→%prod.quarkus.datasource.jdbc.max-size=15\n    24→\n    25→\n    26→# -------------------------------\n    27→# Hibernate ORM\n    28→# -------------------------------\n    29→\n    30→# Load seed data\n    31→%dev.quarkus.hibernate-orm.sql-load-script=import.sql\n    32→%test.quarkus.hibernate-orm.sql-load-script=import.sql\n    33→%prod.quarkus.hibernate-orm.sql-load-script=import.sql\n    34→\n    35→# SQL logging (applies to all profiles)\n    36→quarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=true\n    37→\n    38→# Schema generation (profile-specific)\n    39→%dev.quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\n    40→%test.quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\n    41→%prod.quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=validate\n    42→\n    43→\n    44→# -------------------------------\n    45→# Container image (Jib) + Kubernetes\n    46→# -------------------------------\n    47→quarkus.container-image.group=rhdevelopers\n    48→quarkus.container-image.registry=quay.io\n    49→quarkus.container-image.tag=1.0.0\n    50→\n    51→quarkus.kubernetes.service-type=load-balancer\n    52→\n    53→\n    54→# -------------------------------\n    55→# HTTP + Qute\n    56→# -------------------------------\n    57→quarkus.http.enable-compression=true\n    58→quarkus.http.enable-decompression=true\n    59→quarkus.qute.strict-rendering=true\n    60→\n    61→\n    62→# -------------------------------\n    63→# Misc\n    64→# -------------------------------\n    65→\n    66→# Disable Quarkus build analytics prompt (for non-interactive environments)\n    67→quarkus.analytics.disabled=true\n    68→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YE9jL5iXZnDeazRE2ReELs","session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"7443fb88-c210-4b8a-b93a-59e8f63cd191"}
