{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DyPFPeuRxXuAo5A4Mtmd1o","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Collection;\n     4→import java.util.HashSet;\n     5→import java.util.Set;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.CascadeType;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.FetchType;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    13→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Digits;\n    14→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    16→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.model.Person;\n    17→\n    18→@Entity\n    19→@Table(name = \"owners\")\n    20→public class Owner extends Person {\n    21→\n    22→    @Column(name = \"address\")\n    23→    @NotEmpty\n    24→    @FormParam(\"address\")\n    25→    public String address;\n    26→\n    27→    @Column(name = \"city\")\n    28→    @NotEmpty\n    29→    @FormParam(\"city\")\n    30→    public String city;\n    31→\n    32→    @Column(name = \"telephone\")\n    33→    @NotEmpty\n    34→    @Digits(fraction = 0, integer = 10)\n    35→    @FormParam(\"telephone\")\n    36→    public String telephone;\n    37→\n    38→    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy = \"owner\", fetch = FetchType.EAGER) // it is eager but probably it could be changed to lazy and make some lazy load before rendering template but we might end up in similar performance\n    39→    public Set<Pet> pets;\n    40→\n    41→    public static Collection<Owner> findByLastName(String name) {\n    42→        return Owner.list(\"lastName\", name);\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    public Owner attach() {\n    46→        return getEntityManager().merge(this);\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    @Override\n    50→    public String toString() {\n    51→        return \"Owner [address=\" + address + \", city=\" + city + \", pets=\" + pets + \", telephone=\" + telephone + \"]\";\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public void addPet(Pet pet) {\n    55→        getPetsInternal().add(pet);\n    56→        pet.owner = this;\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    protected Set<Pet> getPetsInternal() {\n    60→\t\tif (this.pets == null) {\n    61→\t\t\tthis.pets = new HashSet<>();\n    62→\t\t}\n    63→\t\treturn this.pets;\n    64→\t}\n    65→\n    66→}\n    67→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YE9jL5iXZnDeazRE2ReELs","session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"1f8fc05f-0288-424a-a0dd-c2b2ff819a71"}
