{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LuZPF7GdY8MWUHwmJpEusx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.qute.i18n.Message;\n     4→import io.quarkus.qute.i18n.MessageBundle;\n     5→\n     6→@MessageBundle\n     7→public interface AppMessages {\n     8→    \n     9→    @Message(\"Find Owner\")\n    10→    String find_owner();\n    11→\n    12→    @Message(\"Last Name\")\n    13→    String last_name();\n    14→\n    15→    @Message(\"Edit Owner\")\n    16→    String edit_owner();\n    17→\n    18→    @Message(\"Add Owner\")\n    19→    String add_owner();\n    20→\n    21→    @Message(\"Find Owners\")\n    22→    String find_owners();\n    23→\n    24→    @Message(\"Name\")\n    25→    String name();\n    26→\n    27→    @Message(\"Address\")\n    28→    String address();\n    29→\n    30→    @Message(\"Telephone\")\n    31→    String telephone();\n    32→\n    33→    @Message(\"City\")\n    34→    String city();\n    35→\n    36→    @Message(\"Pets\")\n    37→    String pets();\n    38→\n    39→    @Message(\"Pet\")\n    40→    String pet();\n    41→\n    42→    @Message(\"Error\")\n    43→    String error();\n    44→\n    45→    @Message(\"None\")\n    46→    String none();\n    47→\n    48→    @Message(\"Veterinarians\")\n    49→    String veterinarians();\n    50→\n    51→    @Message(\"Specialties\")\n    52→    String specialties();\n    53→\n    54→    @Message(\"Welcome\")\n    55→    String welcome();\n    56→\n    57→    @Message(\"Birthdate\")\n    58→    String birthdate();\n    59→\n    60→    @Message(\"Type\")\n    61→    String type();\n    62→\n    63→    @Message(\"Owner\")\n    64→    String owner();\n    65→\n    66→    @Message(\"Edit Pet\")\n    67→    String edit_pet();\n    68→\n    69→    @Message(\"Add Pet\")\n    70→    String add_pet();\n    71→\n    72→    @Message(\"Add Visit\")\n    73→    String add_visit();\n    74→\n    75→    @Message(\"Visit Date\")\n    76→    String visit_date();\n    77→\n    78→    @Message(\"Description\")\n    79→    String description();\n    80→\n    81→    @Message(\"New\")\n    82→    String new_();\n    83→\n    84→    @Message(\"Visit\")\n    85→    String visit();\n    86→\n    87→    @Message(\"Date\")\n    88→    String date();\n    89→\n    90→    @Message(\"Home\")\n    91→    String home();\n    92→\n    93→    @Message(\"Pets and Visits\")\n    94→    String pets_and_visits();\n    95→\n    96→    @Message(\"Previous Visits\")\n    97→    String previous_visits();\n    98→\n    99→    @Message(\"Something happened...\")\n   100→    String something_wrong();\n   101→\n   102→}\n   103→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"81acc606-74e9-4041-ba3d-0b70061edd33"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019VGMZrcLx9JVkrLqX7gNER","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     7→\n     8→@Path(\"/oups\")\n     9→public class CrashResource {\n    10→    \n    11→    @GET\n    12→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    13→    public String triggerException() {\n    14→\t\tthrow new RuntimeException(\n    15→\t\t\t\t\"Expected: controller used to showcase what \" + \"happens when an exception is thrown\");\n    16→\t}\n    17→\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"0eacf111-698f-430e-8137-f68ee0a2d002"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0164KmZEKPSxHof9ncgzuEhy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n     5→import org.jboss.logging.Logger;\n     6→import org.jboss.resteasy.reactive.server.ServerExceptionMapper;\n     7→\n     8→public class ErrorExceptionMapper {\n     9→\n    10→    private static final Logger LOG = Logger.getLogger(ErrorExceptionMapper.class);\n    11→    public static final String ERROR_HEADER = \"x-error\";\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    TemplatesLocale templates;\n    15→\n    16→    @ServerExceptionMapper\n    17→    public Response map(Exception exception) {\n    18→        LOG.error(\"Internal application error\", exception);\n    19→        return Response.ok(templates.error(exception.getMessage())).header(ERROR_HEADER, true).build();\n    20→    }\n    21→\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"5aaa74c5-4ea5-43cb-a014-021521bf000f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01J3RPUHKMwBVFuio84iPU8c","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n     4→import java.util.Locale;\n     5→\n     6→import io.quarkus.qute.Variant;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     8→\n     9→public class LocaleVariantCreator {\n    10→    \n    11→    public static Variant locale(Locale l) {\n    12→        return new Variant(Locale.getDefault(), MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN, StandardCharsets.UTF_8.name());\n    13→    }\n    14→\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"db71489c-ca06-4347-8226-65a330883594"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FSwaosWjFxk14f4i3HnQkD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.qute.i18n.Localized;\n     4→import io.quarkus.qute.i18n.Message;\n     5→\n     6→@Localized(\"es\")\n     7→public interface SpanishAppMessages extends AppMessages {\n     8→    \n     9→    @Override\n    10→    @Message(\"Buscar Propietario\")\n    11→    String find_owner();\n    12→\n    13→    @Override\n    14→    @Message(\"Editar Propietario\")\n    15→    String edit_owner();\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    @Message(\"Apellido\")\n    19→    String last_name();\n    20→\n    21→    @Override\n    22→    @Message(\"Añadir Propietario\")\n    23→    String add_owner();\n    24→\n    25→    @Override\n    26→    @Message(\"Buscar Propietarios\")\n    27→    String find_owners();\n    28→\n    29→    @Override\n    30→    @Message(\"Nombre\")\n    31→    String name();\n    32→\n    33→    @Override\n    34→    @Message(\"Error\")\n    35→    String error();\n    36→\n    37→    @Override\n    38→    @Message(\"Veterinarios\")\n    39→    String veterinarians();\n    40→\n    41→    @Override\n    42→    @Message(\"ninguna\")\n    43→    String none();\n    44→\n    45→    @Override\n    46→    @Message(\"Inicio\")\n    47→    String home();\n    48→\n    49→    @Override\n    50→    @Message(\"Dirección\")\n    51→    String address();\n    52→\n    53→    @Override\n    54→    @Message(\"Teléfono\")\n    55→    String telephone();\n    56→\n    57→    @Override\n    58→    @Message(\"Mascotas\")\n    59→    String pets();\n    60→\n    61→    @Override\n    62→    @Message(\"Especialidades\")\n    63→    String specialties();\n    64→\n    65→    @Override\n    66→    @Message(\"Bienvenidos\")\n    67→    String welcome();\n    68→\n    69→    @Override\n    70→    @Message(\"Ciudad\")\n    71→    String city();\n    72→\n    