{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0129ofnfJpz5Di6noQ2guJAg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base} \n     2→  {#body}\n     3→  <h2>{msg:find_owners}</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  <form action=\"/owners\" method=\"get\"\n     6→    class=\"form-horizontal\" id=\"search-owner-form\">\n     7→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n     8→      <div class=\"control-group\" id=\"lastNameGroup\">\n     9→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:last_name} </label>\n    10→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    11→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" id=\"lastName\" name=\"lastName\" size=\"30\"\n    12→            maxlength=\"80\" />\n    13→            {#if errors.size > 0} \n    14→            <span class=\"help-inline\">\n    15→                <div>\n    16→                    {#for err in errors}\n    17→                        <p>{err}</p>\n    18→                    {/for}\n    19→                </div>\n    20→            </div>\n    21→            </span>\n    22→            {/if}\n    23→        </div>\n    24→      </div>\n    25→    </div>\n    26→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    27→      <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    28→        <button type=\"submit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">{msg:find_owner}</button>\n    29→      </div>\n    30→    </div>\n    31→\n    32→    <a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"/owners/new\">{msg:add_owner}</a>\n    33→\n    34→  </form>\n    35→\n    36→  {/body}\n    37→{/include}\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"892e906d-3d78-4149-ad22-8b8238f40fda"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Qikj4RNNWHqwfhtERpPsFW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base} \n     2→  {#body}\n     3→<h2>Owner Information</h2>\n     4→  \n     5→  \n     6→    <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n     7→      <tr>\n     8→        <th>{msg:name}</th>\n     9→        <td><b>{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</b></td>\n    10→      </tr>\n    11→      <tr>\n    12→        <th>{msg:address}</th>\n    13→        <td>{owner.address}</td>\n    14→      </tr>\n    15→      <tr>\n    16→        <th>{msg:city}</th>\n    17→        <td>{owner.city}</td>\n    18→      </tr>\n    19→      <tr>\n    20→        <th>{msg:telephone}</th>\n    21→        <td>{owner.telephone}</td>\n    22→      </tr>\n    23→    </table>\n    24→  \n    25→    <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/edit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Edit\n    26→      Owner</a>\n    27→    <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/new\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Add\n    28→      New Pet</a>\n    29→  \n    30→    <br />\n    31→    <br />\n    32→    <br />\n    33→    {#if owner.pets}\n    34→    <h2>{msg:pets_and_visits}</h2>\n    35→  \n    36→    <table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    37→        \n    38→      {#for pet in owner.pets}\n    39→      <tr>\n    40→        <td valign=\"top\">\n    41→          <dl class=\"dl-horizontal\">\n    42→            <dt>{msg:name}</dt>\n    43→            <dd>{pet.name}</dd>\n    44→            <dt>{msg:birthdate}</dt>\n    45→            <dd>{pet.birthDate.format()}</dd>\n    46→            <dt>{msg:type}</dt>\n    47→            <dd>{pet.type.stringify}</dd>\n    48→          </dl>\n    49→        </td>\n    50→        <td valign=\"top\">\n    51→          <table class=\"table-condensed\">\n    52→            <thead>\n    53→              <tr>\n    54→                <th>{msg:visit_date}</th>\n    55→                <th>{msg:description}</th>\n    56→              </tr>\n    57→              <tr>\n    58→                <td><a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/{pet.id}/edit\">{msg:edit_pet}</a></td>\n    59→                <td><a\n    60→                  href=\"/owners/{owner.id}/pets/{pet.id}/visits/new\">{msg:add_visit}</a></td>\n    61→              </tr>\n    62→            </thead>\n    63→            {#for visit in pet.sortedVisits}\n    64→            <tr>\n    65→              <td>{visit.date.format()}</td>\n    66→              <td>{visit.description ?: ''}</td>\n    67→            </tr>\n    68→            {/for}\n    69→          </table>\n    70→        </td>\n    71→      </tr>\n    72→      {/for}\n    73→  \n    74→    </table>\n    75→    {/if}\n    76→    {/body}\n    77→    {/include}\n    78→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"ab814cbb-3ebb-4fdf-a988-2a3f28bb409f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012TsYpWJTV2TwvmELAKDqX7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→<h2>Owners</h2>\n     4→\n     5→<table id=\"owners\" class=\"table table-striped\">\n     6→    <thead>\n     7→        <tr>\n     8→            <th style=\"width: 150px;\">{msg:name}</th>\n     9→            <th style=\"width: 200px;\">{msg:address}</th>\n    10→            <th>City</th>\n    11→            <th style=\"width: 120px\">{msg:telephone}</th>\n    12→            <th>{msg:pets}</th>\n    13→        </tr>\n    14→    </thead>\n    15→    <tbody>\n    16→        {#for owner in owners}\n    17→        <tr>\n    18→            <td>\n    19→                <a href=\"/owners/{owner.id}\"/>{owner.firstName} {owner.lastName}</a>\n    20→            </td>\n    21→            <td>{owner.address}</td>\n    22→            <td>{owner.city}</td>\n    23→            <td>{owner.telephone}</td>\n    24→            <td>\n    25→                {#for pet in owner.pets}\n    26→                    <span>{pet.name}</span>\n    27→                {/for}\n    28→            </td>\n    29→        </tr>\n    30→        {/for}\n    31→    </tbody>\n    32→</table>\n    33→{/body}\n    34→{/include}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"f267ea91-94fb-4510-b6dc-297d93c4575b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E3iF5WfZR9rejhedM2vdzJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→<h2>{msg:veterinarians}</h2>\n     4→\n     5→<table id=\"vets\" class=\"table table-striped\">\n     6→    <thead>\n     7→        <tr>\n     8→            <th>{msg:name}</th>\n     9→            <th>{msg:specialties}</th>\n    10→        </tr>\n    11→    </thead>\n    12→    <tbody>\n    13→        {#for vet in vets}\n    14→        <tr>\n    15→            <td>{vet.firstName} {vet.lastName}</td>\n    16→            <td>\n    17→                {#for s in vet.specialties}\n    18→                <span>\n    19→                    {s.name}&nbsp;\n    20→                </span>\n    21→                {/for}\n    22→\n    23→                <span>{#if vet.nrOfSpecialties == 0}{msg:none}{/if}</span>\n    24→            </td>\n    25→        </tr>\n    26→        {/for}\n    27→    </tbody>\n    28→</table>\n    29→{/body}\n    30→{/include}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"d6605b98-4bd1-4cce-bb51-6010c074a897"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VfSukQxBS3SfhAjTPbCkaq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→<h2>{msg:owner}</h2>\n     4→<form class=\"form-horizontal\" id=\"add-owner-form\" method=\"post\">\n     5→    <div class=\"form-group has-feedback\">\n     6→\n     7→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('firstName') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n     8→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:name}</label>\n     9→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    10→                <div>\n    11→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"firstName\" name=\"firstName\" value=\"{owner.firstName ?: ''}\" />\n    12→\n    13→                </div>\n    14→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('firstName') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    15→                {#if errors.containsKey('firstName') != null}\n    16→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('firstName')}</span>\n    17→                {/if}\n    18→            </div>\n    19→        </div>\n    20→\n    21→\n    22→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('lastName') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    23→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:last_name}</label>\n    24→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    25→                <div>\n    26→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"lastName\" name=\"lastName\" value=\"{owner.lastName ?: ''}\" />\n    27→\n    28→                </div>\n    29→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('firstName') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    30→                {#if errors.containsKey('lastName') != null}\n    31→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('lastName')}</span>\n    32→                {/if}\n    33→            </div>\n    34→        </div>\n    35→\n    36→\n    37→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('address') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    38→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:address}</label>\n    39→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    40→                <div>\n    41→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"address\" name=\"address\" value=\"{owner.address ?: ''}\" />\n    42→\n    43→                </div>\n    44→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('address') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    45→                {#if errors.containsKey('address') != null}\n    46→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('address')}</span>\n    47→                {/if}\n    48→            </div>\n    49→        </div>\n    50→\n    51→\n    52→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('city') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    53→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:city}</label>\n    54→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    55→                <div>\n    56→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"city\" name=\"city\" value=\"{owner.city ?: ''}\" />\n    57→\n    58→                </div>\n    59→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('city') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    60→                {#if errors.containsKey('city') != null}\n    61→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('city')}</span>\n    62→                {/if}\n    63→            </div>\n    64→        </div>\n    65→\n    66→\n    67→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('telephone') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    68→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:telephone}</label>\n    69→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    70→                <div>\n    71→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"telephone\" name=\"telephone\" value=\"{owner.telephone ?: ''}\" />\n    72→\n    73→                </div>\n    74→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('telephone') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    75→                {#if errors.containsKey('telephone') != null}\n    76→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('telephone')}</span>\n    77→                {/if}\n    78→            </div>\n    79→        </div>\n    80→\n    81→    </div>\n    82→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    83→        <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    84→            <button class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"submit\">\n    85→                {#if owner}\n    86→                {msg:edit_owner}\n    87→                {#else}\n    88→                {msg:add_owner}\n    89→                {/if}\n    90→            </button>\n    91→        </div>\n    92→    </div>\n    93→</form>\n    94→{/body}\n    95→{/include}\n    96→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"d09678c0-c639-4d44-82ea-e73abca943f4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SV8LyXx1JLtyv7kvFcpyNh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→<h2>\n     4→    {#if !pet}{msg:new_}{/if}\n     5→    {msg:pet}\n     6→  </h2>\n     7→  <form class=\"form-horizontal\" method=\"post\">\n     8→    <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"id\" value=\"\" />\n     9→    <div class=\"form-group has-feedback\">\n    10→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    11→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:owner}</label>\n    12→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    13→          <span>{owner.firstName}</span>\n    14→        </div>\n    15→      </div>\n    16→      \n    17→      <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('name') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    18→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:name}</label>\n    19→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    20→            <div>\n    21→                <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"name\" name=\"name\" value=\"{pet.name ?: ''}\"/>\n    22→            </div>\n    23→          <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('name') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\"\n    24→            aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    25→            {#if errors.containsKey('name') != null}\n    26→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('name')}</span>\n    27→            {/if}\n    28→        </div>\n    29→      </div>\n    30→      \n    31→      <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('birthDate') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    32→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:birthdate}</label>\n    33→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    34→            <div>\n    35→                <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"YYYY-MM-DD\" title=\"Enter a date in this format: YYYY-MM-DD\" id=\"birthDate\" name=\"birthDate\" value=\"{pet.birthDate ?: ''}\"/>\n    36→            </div>\n    37→          <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('birthDate') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\"\n    38→            aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    39→            {#if errors.containsKey('birthDate') != null}\n    40→              <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('birthDate')}</span>\n    41→            {/if}\n    42→        </div>\n    43→      </div>\n    44→    \n    45→      \n    46→      <div class=\"form-group\">\n    47→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:type}</label>\n    48→\n    49→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    50→          <select id=\"type\" name=\"type\">\n    51→            {#for petType in petTypes}\n    52→            <option value=\"{petType.name}\" {#if petType.name == pet.type.name} selected {/if}>{petType.name}</option>\n    53→            {/for}\n    54→          </select>\n    55→          <span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-ok form-control-feedback\"\n    56→            aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    57→          \n    58→        </div>\n    59→      </div>\n    60→    \n    61→    </div>\n    62→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    63→      <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    64→        <button\n    65→          class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"submit\">\n    66→          {#if pet}\n    67→          {msg:edit_pet}\n    68→          {#else}\n    69→          {msg:add_pet}\n    70→          {/if}\n    71→        </button>\n    72→      </div>\n    73→    </div>\n    74→  </form>\n    75→  {/body}\n    76→  {/include}\n    77→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"323d542f-0db1-41c3-878e-cdbee3f05755"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WxuhQgQfPgnF8uq419vbFA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→<h2>\n     4→    {#if !visit}{msg:new_} {/if}\n     5→    {msg:visit}\n     6→</h2>\n     7→\n     8→<b>Pet</b>\n     9→<table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    10→    <thead>\n    11→        <tr>\n    12→            <th>{msg:name}</th>\n    13→            <th>{msg:birthdate}</th>\n    14→            <th>{msg:type}</th>\n    15→            <th>{msg:owner}</th>\n    16→        </tr>\n    17→    </thead>\n    18→    <tr>\n    19→        <td>{pet.name}</td>\n    20→        <td>{pet.birthDate.format()}</td>\n    21→        <td>{pet.type.name}</td>\n    22→        <td>{pet.owner.firstName} {pet.owner.lastName}</td>\n    23→    </tr>\n    24→</table>\n    25→\n    26→<form class=\"form-horizontal\" method=\"post\">\n    27→    <div class=\"form-group has-feedback\">\n    28→\n    29→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('date') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    30→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:date}</label>\n    31→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    32→                <div>\n    33→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"YYYY-MM-DD\"\n    34→                        id=\"date\" name=\"date\" value=\"{visit.date ?: ''}\"/>\n    35→                </div>\n    36→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('date') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    37→                {#if errors.containsKey('date') != null}\n    38→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('date')}</span>\n    39→                {/if}\n    40→            </div>\n    41→        </div>\n    42→\n    43→\n    44→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('description') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    45→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:description}</label>\n    46→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    47→                <div>\n    48→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"description\" name=\"description\" value=\"{visit.description ?: ''}\" />\n    49→                </div>\n    50→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('description') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    51→                {#if errors.containsKey('description') != null}\n    52→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('description')}</span>\n    53→                {/if}\n    54→            </div>\n    55→        </div>\n    56→\n    57→    </div>\n    58→\n    59→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    60→        <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    61→            <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"petId\" value=\"1\" />\n    62→            <button class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"submit\">{msg:add_visit}</button>\n    63→        </div>\n    64→    </div>\n    65→</form>\n    66→\n    67→<br />\n    68→<b>{msg:previous_visits}</b>\n    69→<table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    70→    <tr>\n    71→        <th>{msg:date}</th>\n    72→        <th>{msg:description}</th>\n    73→    </tr>\n    74→    <tr>\n    75→        {#if visit}\n    76→        {#for v in pet.sortedVisits}\n    77→        <td>{v.date.format()}</td>\n    78→        <td>{v.description}</td>\n    79→        {/for}\n    80→        {/if}\n    81→    </tr>\n    82→</table>\n    83→{/body}\n    84→{/include}\n    85→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"fba85913-93ec-4485-bf15-a3a5f352052a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01T8ZvvyvjcpemEsDvcrQuBs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base} \n     2→  {#body}\n     3→  <h2>{msg:welcome}</h2>\n     4→  <div class=\"row\">\n     5→      <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n     6→        <img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"../images/pets.png\"/>\n     7→        <h2>{msg:error}</h2>\n     8→        <p>{msg:something_wrong}</p>\n     9→      </div>\n    10→  </div>\n    11→  {/body}\n    12→{/include}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"f7a943f8-bf67-4b13-b30e-6c677371a1e0"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MSikBkG9kk1GizueEUnsAN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the migration in detail.\n\n**Analysis Summary:**\n- This is a Quarkus 3.30.5 PetClinic application using:\n  - Quarkus REST (JAX-RS implementation) with RESTEasy Reactive  \n  - Hibernate ORM with Panache (Quarkus-specific active record pattern)\n  - Qute template engine (Quarkus-specific)\n  - H2 for dev/test, PostgreSQL for prod\n  - Quarkus-specific annotations: `@Blocking`, `@ServerExceptionMapper`, `@CheckedTemplate`, `@TemplateExtension`, `@MessageBundle`, etc.\n  - Quarkus dependency injection (CDI)\n\n**Migration to \"Jakarta\" means:** Converting to a standard Jakarta EE application server runtime (like WildFly or Open Liberty or a standalone approach). The most practical approach is to use a lightweight Jakarta EE-compatible framework. Since the task says \"jakarta\", I'll migrate to a standard Jakarta EE WAR deployment on WildFly/Open Liberty, or alternatively use a standalone approach with standard Jakarta EE APIs.\n\nThe most practical migration path: **Convert to a standard Jakarta EE application using WildFly** (a mature Jakarta EE-compatible server), replacing Quarkus-specific APIs with standard Jakarta EE equivalents:\n- Quarkus Panache → Standard JPA with EntityManager\n- Qute templates → Jakarta Server Pages (JSP) or standard templating (Thymeleaf with JAX-RS)\n- Quarkus REST → Standard JAX-RS\n- Quarkus CDI → Standard CDI\n- `@ServerExceptionMapper` → Standard JAX-RS `ExceptionMapper`\n- `@CheckedTemplate` / Qute → We'll use a simple template approach\n\nLet me update my plan and start the migration:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8014,"cache_read_input_tokens":54860,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8014,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":900},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"25e4979d-e521-485a-bc0d-8e1e512c9363"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MSikBkG9kk1GizueEUnsAN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_012ZtsVph1U36Co8SAffRpDq","name":"TodoWrite","input":{"todos":[{"content":"Analyze existing codebase structure","status":"completed","activeForm":"Analyzing existing codebase structure"},{"content":"Generate smoke tests for original functionality","status":"in_progress","activeForm":"Generating smoke tests"},{"content":"Rewrite pom.xml for Jakarta EE (WildFly)","status":"pending","activeForm":"Rewriting pom.xml for Jakarta EE"},{"content":"Replace Panache entities with standard JPA entities","status":"pending","activeForm":"Replacing Panache entities with standard JPA entities"},{"content":"Replace Qute templates with JSP templates","status":"pending","activeForm":"Replacing Qute templates with JSP templates"},{"content":"Convert Resource classes to standard JAX-RS","status":"pending","activeForm":"Converting Resource classes to standard JAX-RS"},{"content":"Create persistence.xml for standard JPA","status":"pending","activeForm":"Creating persistence.xml for standard JPA"},{"content":"Update configuration files","status":"pending","activeForm":"Updating configuration files"},{"content":"Update Dockerfile for WildFly","status":"pending","activeForm":"Updating Dockerfile for WildFly"},{"content":"Build Docker image and run container","status":"pending","activeForm":"Building Docker image and running container"},{"content":"Execute smoke tests against running container","status":"pending","activeForm":"Executing smoke tests"},{"content":"Document all actions in CHANGELOG.md","status":"pending","activeForm":"Documenting actions in CHANGELOG.md"}]}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8014,"cache_read_input_tokens":54860,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8014,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":900},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"e8e93796-cf9d-44a1-8636-d598b4da8797"}
