{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GAJtRwwNJQmHuJyUhKx2Ss","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.jakarta.samples.petclinic;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→@ApplicationPath(\"/api\")\n     7→public class JaxRsApplication extends Application {\n     8→}\n     9→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"b740b46f-c1e5-4f61-8153-eae02219064d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDKD1k52vD6KqYci9UfCia","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.jakarta.samples.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→\n    12→@Path(\"/vets\")\n    13→public class VetResource {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    EntityManager em;\n    17→\n    18→    @GET\n    19→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    20→    public Vets showResourcesVetList() {\n    21→        Vets vets = new Vets();\n    22→        List<Vet> vetList = em.createQuery(\"SELECT v FROM Vet v\", Vet.class).getResultList();\n    23→        vets.getVetList().addAll(vetList);\n    24→        return vets;\n    25→    }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"540dd812-c4a3-434d-af38-6c88f9f8834a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014oxRaToMGEyCYvR4eH8rQa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.jakarta.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→\n    12→@Path(\"/owners\")\n    13→public class OwnersResource {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    EntityManager em;\n    17→\n    18→    @GET\n    19→    @Path(\"/list\")\n    20→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    21→    public List<Owner> listOwners() {\n    22→        return em.createQuery(\"SELECT o FROM Owner o\", Owner.class).getResultList();\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"c2a59697-02d0-4280-8997-f230174387b0"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_011kMK5pW2q1t9UJJPjTzLnq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the URL structure on WildFly:\n- HTML pages: `/petclinic/` (welcome), `/petclinic/owners/...`, `/petclinic/vets.html`, `/petclinic/oups`\n- JSON APIs: `/petclinic/api/vets`, `/petclinic/api/owners/list`\n\nLet me also check the OwnersServlet to see how it handles the `/owners/api/list` redirect:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1690,"cache_read_input_tokens":30242,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1690,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":239},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"01c4feed-3947-4bec-8df2-5d2be26c5fdf"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_011kMK5pW2q1t9UJJPjTzLnq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01JkUDfmnsapZYrLEx5U3aLv","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/jakarta/samples/petclinic/owner/OwnersServlet.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1690,"cache_read_input_tokens":30242,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1690,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":239},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"1c487523-e67f-4800-bf64-fe5565c2ce5f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JkUDfmnsapZYrLEx5U3aLv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.jakarta.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     5→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n     6→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n     7→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n     8→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n     9→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    10→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    11→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n    12→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n    13→import org.jakarta.samples.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    14→\n    15→import java.io.IOException;\n    16→import java.util.Collection;\n    17→import java.util.HashMap;\n    18→import java.util.List;\n    19→import java.util.Map;\n    20→import java.util.Set;\n    21→\n    22→@WebServlet(\"/owners/*\")\n    23→public class OwnersServlet extends HttpServlet {\n    24→\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    EntityManager em;\n    27→\n    28→    @Inject\n    29→    Validator validator;\n    30→\n    31→    @Override\n    32→    protected void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    33→        String pathInfo = req.getPathInfo();\n    34→\n    35→        if (pathInfo == null || pathInfo.equals(\"/\")) {\n    36→            // Process find form: GET /owners?lastName=\n    37→            processFindForm(req, resp);\n    38→        } else if (pathInfo.equals(\"/find\")) {\n    39→            // Show find form\n    40→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", java.util.Collections.emptyList());\n    41→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/findOwners.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n    42→        } else if (pathInfo.equals(\"/new\")) {\n    43→            // Show create form\n    44→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", null);\n    45→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", new HashMap<String, String>());\n    46→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdateOwnerForm.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n    47→        } else if (pathInfo.matches(\"/\\\\d+/edit\")) {\n    48→            Long ownerId = extractId(pathInfo, 1);\n    49→            Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n    50→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n    51→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", new HashMap<String, String>());\n    52→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdateOwnerForm.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n    53→        } else if (pathInfo.matches(\"/\\\\d+/pets/new\")) {\n    54→            Long ownerId = extractId(pathInfo, 1);\n    55→            Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n    56→            List<PetType> petTypes = em.createQuery(\"SELECT pt FROM PetType pt\", PetType.class).getResultList();\n    57→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n    58→            req.setAttribute(\"pet\", null);\n    59→            req.setAttribute(\"petTypes\", petTypes);\n    60→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", new HashMap<String, String>());\n    61→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdatePetForm.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n    62→        } else if (pathInfo.matches(\"/\\\\d+/pets/\\\\d+/edit\")) {\n    63→            String[] parts = pathInfo.split(\"/\");\n    64→            Long ownerId = Long.parseLong(parts[1]);\n    65→            Long petId = Long.parseLong(parts[3]);\n    66→            Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n    67→            Pet pet = em.find(Pet.class, petId);\n    68→            List<PetType> petTypes = em.createQuery(\"SELECT pt FROM PetType pt\", PetType.class).getResultList();\n    69→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n    70→            req.setAttribute(\"pet\", pet);\n    71→            req.setAttribute(\"petTypes\", petTypes);\n    72→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", new HashMap<String, String>());\n    73→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdatePetForm.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n    74→        } else if (pathInfo.matches(\"/\\\\d+/pets/\\\\d+/visits/new\")) {\n    75→            String[] parts = pathInfo.split(\"/\");\n    76→            Long petId = Long.parseLong(parts[3]);\n    77→            Pet pet = em.find(Pet.class, petId);\n    78→            req.setAttribute(\"pet\", pet);\n    79→            req.setAttribute(\"visit\", null);\n    80→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", new HashMap<String, String>());\n    81→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdateVisitForm.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n    82→        } else if (pathInfo.matches(\"/api/list\")) {\n    83→            // JSON API - delegate to JAX-RS\n    84→            resp.sendRedirect(req.getContextPath() + \"/api/owners/list\");\n    85→        } else if (pathInfo.matches(\"/\\\\d+\")) {\n    86→            Long ownerId = extractId(pathInfo, 1);\n    87→            Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n    88→            if (owner == null) {\n    89→                req.setAttribute(\"message\", \"Owner not found\");\n    90→                resp.setHeader(\"x-error\", \"true\");\n    91→                req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/error.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n    92→                return;\n    93→            }\n    94→            setVisits(owner);\n    95→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n    96→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n    97→        } else {\n    98→            resp.sendError(404);\n    99→        }\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    @Override\n   103→    @Transactional\n   104→    protected void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   105→        String pathInfo = req.getPathInfo();\n   106→\n   107→        if (pathInfo != null && pathInfo.equals(\"/new\")) {\n   108→            processCreateOwner(req, resp);\n   109→        } else if (pathInfo != null && pathInfo.matches(\"/\\\\d+/edit\")) {\n   110→            Long ownerId = extractId(pathInfo, 1);\n   111→            processUpdateOwner(req, resp, ownerId);\n   112→        } else if (pathInfo != null && pathInfo.matches(\"/\\\\d+/pets/new\")) {\n   113→            Long ownerId = extractId(pathInfo, 1);\n   114→            processCreatePet(req, resp, ownerId);\n   115→        } else if (pathInfo != null && pathInfo.matches(\"/\\\\d+/pets/\\\\d+/edit\")) {\n   116→            String[] parts = pathInfo.split(\"/\");\n   117→            Long ownerId = Long.parseLong(parts[1]);\n   118→            Long petId = Long.parseLong(parts[3]);\n   119→            processUpdatePet(req, resp, ownerId, petId);\n   120→        } else if (pathInfo != null && pathInfo.matches(\"/\\\\d+/pets/\\\\d+/visits/new\")) {\n   121→            String[] parts = pathInfo.split(\"/\");\n   122→            Long ownerId = Long.parseLong(parts[1]);\n   123→            Long petId = Long.parseLong(parts[3]);\n   124→            processCreateVisit(req, resp, ownerId, petId);\n   125→        } else {\n   126→            resp.sendError(404);\n   127→        }\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    private void processFindForm(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   131→        String lastName = req.getParameter(\"lastName\");\n   132→\n   133→        Collection<Owner> owners;\n   134→        if (lastName == null || lastName.trim().isEmpty()) {\n   135→            owners = em.createQuery(\"SELECT o FROM Owner o\", Owner.class).getResultList();\n   136→        } else {\n   137→            owners = em.createQuery(\"SELECT o FROM Owner o WHERE o.lastName = :lastName\", Owner.class)\n   138→                    .setParameter(\"lastName\", lastName)\n   139→                    .getResultList();\n   140→        }\n   141→\n   142→        if (owners.isEmpty()) {\n   143→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", java.util.Arrays.asList(\"lastName not found\"));\n   144→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/findOwners.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   145→        } else if (owners.size() == 1) {\n   146→            Owner owner = owners.iterator().next();\n   147→            setVisits(owner);\n   148→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n   149→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   150→        } else {\n   151→            req.setAttribute(\"owners\", owners);\n   152→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownersList.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   153→        }\n   154→    }\n   155→\n   156→    @Transactional\n   157→    private void processCreateOwner(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   158→        Owner owner = new Owner();\n   159→        owner.firstName = req.getParameter(\"firstName\");\n   160→        owner.lastName = req.getParameter(\"lastName\");\n   161→        owner.address = req.getParameter(\"address\");\n   162→        owner.city = req.getParameter(\"city\");\n   163→        owner.telephone = req.getParameter(\"telephone\");\n   164→\n   165→        Set<ConstraintViolation<Owner>> violations = validator.validate(owner);\n   166→        Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n   167→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   168→            for (ConstraintViolation<Owner> violation : violations) {\n   169→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   170→            }\n   171→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", null);\n   172→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", errors);\n   173→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdateOwnerForm.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   174→        } else {\n   175→            em.persist(owner);\n   176→            em.flush();\n   177→            setVisits(owner);\n   178→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n   179→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   180→        }\n   181→    }\n   182→\n   183→    @Transactional\n   184→    private void processUpdateOwner(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, Long ownerId) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   185→        Owner owner = new Owner();\n   186→        owner.id = ownerId;\n   187→        owner.firstName = req.getParameter(\"firstName\");\n   188→        owner.lastName = req.getParameter(\"lastName\");\n   189→        owner.address = req.getParameter(\"address\");\n   190→        owner.city = req.getParameter(\"city\");\n   191→        owner.telephone = req.getParameter(\"telephone\");\n   192→\n   193→        Set<ConstraintViolation<Owner>> violations = validator.validate(owner);\n   194→        Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n   195→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   196→            for (ConstraintViolation<Owner> violation : violations) {\n   197→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   198→            }\n   199→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n   200→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", errors);\n   201→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdateOwnerForm.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   202→        } else {\n   203→            Owner merged = em.merge(owner);\n   204→            setVisits(merged);\n   205→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", merged);\n   206→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   207→        }\n   208→    }\n   209→\n   210→    @Transactional\n   211→    private void processCreatePet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, Long ownerId) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   212→        Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n   213→        Pet pet = new Pet();\n   214→        pet.name = req.getParameter(\"name\");\n   215→        String birthDateStr = req.getParameter(\"birthDate\");\n   216→        if (birthDateStr != null && !birthDateStr.trim().isEmpty()) {\n   217→            pet.birthDate = java.time.LocalDate.parse(birthDateStr);\n   218→        }\n   219→        String typeName = req.getParameter(\"type\");\n   220→        pet.type = findPetType(typeName);\n   221→\n   222→        Set<ConstraintViolation<Pet>> violations = validator.validate(pet);\n   223→        Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n   224→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   225→            for (ConstraintViolation<Pet> violation : violations) {\n   226→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   227→            }\n   228→            List<PetType> petTypes = em.createQuery(\"SELECT pt FROM PetType pt\", PetType.class).getResultList();\n   229→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n   230→            req.setAttribute(\"pet\", null);\n   231→            req.setAttribute(\"petTypes\", petTypes);\n   232→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", errors);\n   233→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdatePetForm.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   234→        } else {\n   235→            pet.owner = owner;\n   236→            em.persist(pet);\n   237→            owner.addPet(pet);\n   238→            setVisits(owner);\n   239→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n   240→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   241→        }\n   242→    }\n   243→\n   244→    @Transactional\n   245→    private void processUpdatePet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, Long ownerId, Long petId) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   246→        Pet pet = new Pet();\n   247→        pet.id = petId;\n   248→        pet.name = req.getParameter(\"name\");\n   249→        String birthDateStr = req.getParameter(\"birthDate\");\n   250→        if (birthDateStr != null && !birthDateStr.trim().isEmpty()) {\n   251→            pet.birthDate = java.time.LocalDate.parse(birthDateStr);\n   252→        }\n   253→        String typeName = req.getParameter(\"type\");\n   254→        pet.type = findPetType(typeName);\n   255→\n   256→        Set<ConstraintViolation<Pet>> violations = validator.validate(pet);\n   257→        Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n   258→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   259→            for (ConstraintViolation<Pet> violation : violations) {\n   260→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   261→            }\n   262→            Pet oldPet = em.find(Pet.class, petId);\n   263→            List<PetType> petTypes = em.createQuery(\"SELECT pt FROM PetType pt\", PetType.class).getResultList();\n   264→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", oldPet.owner);\n   265→            req.setAttribute(\"pet\", oldPet);\n   266→            req.setAttribute(\"petTypes\", petTypes);\n   267→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", errors);\n   268→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdatePetForm.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   269→        } else {\n   270→            Pet merged = em.merge(pet);\n   271→            Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n   272→            setVisits(owner);\n   273→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n   274→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   275→        }\n   276→    }\n   277→\n   278→    @Transactional\n   279→    private void processCreateVisit(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, Long ownerId, Long petId) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   280→        Pet pet = em.find(Pet.class, petId);\n   281→        Visit visit = new Visit();\n   282→        String dateStr = req.getParameter(\"date\");\n   283→        if (dateStr != null && !dateStr.trim().isEmpty()) {\n   284→            visit.date = java.time.LocalDate.parse(dateStr);\n   285→        }\n   286→        visit.description = req.getParameter(\"description\");\n   287→        visit.petId = petId;\n   288→\n   289→        Set<ConstraintViolation<Visit>> violations = validator.validate(visit);\n   290→        Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n   291→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   292→            for (ConstraintViolation<Visit> violation : violations) {\n   293→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   294→            }\n   295→            req.setAttribute(\"pet\", pet);\n   296→            req.setAttribute(\"visit\", visit);\n   297→            req.setAttribute(\"errors\", errors);\n   298→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdateVisitForm.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   299→        } else {\n   300→            em.persist(visit);\n   301→            pet.addVisit(visit);\n   302→            Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n   303→            setVisits(owner);\n   304→            req.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n   305→            req.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(req, resp);\n   306→        }\n   307→    }\n   308→\n   309→    private void setVisits(Owner owner) {\n   310→        if (owner != null && owner.pets != null) {\n   311→            for (Pet pet : owner.pets) {\n   312→                List<Visit> visits = em.createQuery(\"SELECT v FROM Visit v WHERE v.petId = :petId\", Visit.class)\n   313→                        .setParameter(\"petId\", pet.id)\n   314→                        .getResultList();\n   315→                pet.setVisitsInternal(visits);\n   316→            }\n   317→        }\n   318→    }\n   319→\n   320→    private PetType findPetType(String name) {\n   321→        List<PetType> types = em.createQuery(\"SELECT pt FROM PetType pt WHERE pt.name = :name\", PetType.class)\n   322→                .setParameter(\"name\", name)\n   323→                .getResultList();\n   324→        if (types.isEmpty()) {\n   325→            throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"type not found: \" + name);\n   326→        }\n   327→        return types.get(0);\n   328→    }\n   329→\n   330→    private Long extractId(String pathInfo, int position) {\n   331→        String[] parts = pathInfo.split(\"/\");\n   332→        return Long.parseLong(parts[position]);\n   333→    }\n   334→}\n   335→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"0592dbea-5884-4410-8f9e-d0959692fb74"}
