{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_016QhgmZ3oQRtncN5E4rnm7r","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. Now I also need to check if there's a potential issue with the `@Transactional` annotation on private methods in the OwnersServlet. In Jakarta EE, `@Transactional` on private methods won't work because CDI interceptors only apply to business methods (non-private). The `doPost` method is annotated but the private `processCreate*` methods also have `@Transactional` which won't work. The `doPost` being `@Transactional` should cover the nested calls though. Let me verify this isn't going to be a problem by checking if the container manages the transaction correctly from doPost.\n\nActually, the main issue is that Servlets managed by the container might not be CDI beans by default. `@Transactional` might not be intercepted. Let me check if this was already working in the previous test. Let me look at whether there's a simpler approach - we can use `UserTransaction` directly, or we need to make sure the servlet is a CDI bean.\n\nActually, in WildFly, servlets with `@Inject` work because WildFly supports CDI injection into servlets. And `@Transactional` on the `doPost` method should be intercepted. The private methods' `@Transactional` annotations are indeed ineffective, but since `doPost` is transactional, all the work inside it will be within that transaction. This should be fine.\n\nNow let me rebuild the Docker image:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4380,"cache_read_input_tokens":40391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4380,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":860},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7f97aa4-1c2c-44bf-80a1-31ac11b107ff","uuid":"b14b6253-514d-46b7-957d-23ab8615d069"}
